column58: Includes area of Etruscan culture in central Italy, particularly confederation of 12 city states; Etruscans possibly arrived from Asia Minor in 9th century BCE, or were of local origins; modern scholars believe they include early Villanovan culture; economy was based on agriculture, mining iron and copper, and harvesting forests; was noted as fierce maritime power; flourished in the 7th-3rd centuries BCE, culture had been absorbed by Roman culture by 1st century BCE.

column60: Is in Spreti.  Florentine noble family that goes back to 14th c.  The family altar in San Pier Maggiore had a polyptych by Lippo di Benivieni with predella added by Benozzo Gozzoli.  When church destroyed ca. 1784 polyptych moved to Palazzo Alessandri.  Main body of polyptych is still in the family collection; predella panels were sold by Cosimo degli Alessandri in 1915 (now in NY Met).  There was also a triptych by Filippo Lippi painted for the church at Villa Alessandri; it was moved to the Florence house ca. 1790 and was also sold by Cosimo degli Alessandri in 1912. MH
